title: For the ladies: Defensive Pistol Skills training class by Rochester Personal Defense, LLC
postcontent:
Now: A defensive pistol training class - for the ladies!!!!

We all know that there are certain things that spouses or significant others should not teach each other or discuss, right? They usually include: driving lessons, politics, wallpapering or painting, and firearms. Why not come out and learn from some easy going, approachable, competent, friendly, and non-testosterone charged instructors?

Learning to handle a pistol is one of the most satisfying, empowering things that you can do.

The instructors of Rochester Personal Defense, LLC have taken the Defensive Firearms Skills Classes 1 and 2 and combined them into Defensive Firearms Shooting Skills 101 Firearms Training

* Firearm safety
* Legalities and justification in self defense (Article 35)
* Deescalation and disengagement from an encounter
* Verbal commands
* Drawing the handgun effectively and safely
* Trigger control and manipulation
* Malfunctions and stoppage clearing
* Tactical vs combat reloading
* Movement and shooting while moving

You will get to practice all of the skills with an unloaded handgun until you are comfortable, then you will get to go live on the range.

Note: This is not a basic level class. If you have never fired or used a handgun before, you should either attend an NRA Basic Pistol class or obtain similar training before attending this class. You must be completely familiar and comfortable with your handgun in order to attend the DPS 101 class. All attendees will be asked to provide verifiable experience. If you have any questions, call before registering.

Equipment needed: Eye and ear protection, A working and reliable firearm, 200 rounds of ammunition, 3 magazines or speedloaders with holders, a quality strong side type holster, comfortable clothing (comfy shoes and appropriate clothing).


Date: August 1st, 2009 8am - 6pm (Saturday)

Location:The Genesee Conservation League,
1570 Old Penfield Rd, Rochester, NY 14625
Cost: $85.00

To register, go to:
http://www.safeinrochester.com/womensclasses.html

Or email us at REDACTED

title: full auto parts +no tax stamp=jail
postcontent:
There exist two kinds of parts kits:

	1. Registered Auto-Sear ( Which, by ATF regulations, is a
	   machinegun all by its self.) Plus other misc. parts like
	   a bolt carrier, disconnector, selector, etc.  The REGISTERED
	   auto-sear IS a machinegun.  Therefore this truely isn't
	   a parts kit but is actually a complete gun.  A Class II
	   manufacturer may assemble these parts with a semi-auto
	   firearm to create a working gun.  If the auto-sear was
	   registered prior to May 19th 1986 this weapon may be owned
	   by the general public.  If it was registered after May
	   19th 1986 it is non transferable and may NOT be owned by
	   civilians.

	2. All parts are unregistered.  This kit contains all the
	   same parts including an auto-sear, but this sear is NOT
	   registered.  ATF does not consider the sear to be a
	   machinegun.  However, if you own this kit AND a semi auto
	   firearm that will accept it, then by ATF definitions you
	   are in possession of a machinegun.

title: Utah Non Resident permit By Rochester Personal Defense, LLC
postcontent:
Do you travel a lot? Want to carry your handgun legally in 30 states? The State of Utah has redone their Non Resident Permit process and you get the benefit. We are now certified to instruct you in the legalities and carrying of a firearm in Utah as well as the other states that honor the Utah Non-Resident Permit. If you travel a lot, the non-resident permits are a big help if you decide to carry or wish to carry where you want to go. Note: the Utah permit is NOT VALID IN NEW YORK STATE.

NOTE: This class will cover ONLY the laws and regulations concerning the State of Utah. We will not be discussing New York State laws or other states' laws. If you possess a NY State Pistol Permit, thank you, but it will neither help you nor hurt you when applying for the Utah permit. There is no way to obtain a waiver or exclusion to the lecture. Utah requires you to attend no matter what your experience or training is.

Classes are currently available from Rochester Personal Defense, LLC in the following areas: Rochester, Syracuse, Binghamton, Middletown, Dansville, Penfield, Henrietta, Brockport, Batavia, Auburn, Oswego, Watertown, Waterloo, Chenango County, Broome County, Tioga County, Monroe County, Northern Pennsylvania, AND MORE!!!!

We will be doing your passport style photos, processing your fingerprints, and we have a notary available. All you have to do is attend, add a copy of your NY drivers license, a check made payable to the Utah BCI for $65.25, and fill everything out and drop your completed application (with your payment) in the mail. We even give you the pre addressed envelope!!

The cost of the permit itself is only $65.20 and it is valid for 5 years. Note: the class fee does not include the cost of the permit.

There are some disqualifiers too. (DWI's within 10 yrs, etc) Please contact us if you have any questions before registering. (We'd hate to have you come attend and be surprised).

The following states currently honor the Utah Non Resident permit: Alabama, Alaska, Arizona, Arkansas, Delaware, Georgia, Idaho, Indiana, Kentucky, Louisiana, Minnesota, Mississippi, Missouri, Montana, New Mexico, North Carolina, North Dakota, Ohio, Oklahoma, Pennsylvania, South Dakota, Tennessee, Texas, Utah, Utah, Vermont, Virginia, Washington, West Virginia, Wyoming (info taken from www.USAcarry.com, 3-16-09)

Upcoming lecture dates: 

Watertown, NY: October 24, 2009 at the Gander Mountain Store in the Salmon Run Mall.

Contact Rochester Personal Defense,LLC for more details at REDACTED or REDACTED

title: Springfield XD 40 Service 4" pistol
postcontent:
I am selling a Springfield XD 40cal Service (4in barrel) pistol with original box and accessories plus additional magazines and two-magazine pouch. For those of you unfamiliar with the XD pistol, it is a modern semi-automatic pistol that generally considered a very reliable and accurate weapon.

You should do your own due diligence as this is a popular pistol and widely documented on the internet, but here are two links to a torture test and stress test: 
http://springfield-armory.primediaoutdoors.com/SPstory11.php
http://springfield-armory.primediaoutdoors.com/SPstory02.php

I am selling everything below as a complete package:

XD40 pistol
XD gear (holster, magazine loader, two-magazine pouch)
original box (manual, lock, test fired cartridge, test fire date is 10-2008)
5 magazines (2 that came with the pistol, 3 other Springfield factory magazines; two of these are brand new and unused)
an extra two-magazine pouch

Around here you can get an XD40 pistol brand new-in-box with two mags for $499 plus tax.  New factory magazines go for about $25, so for three mags is $75.  Assuming 8% sales tax, that's comes out to about $620 out the door if you were to buy brand new.

I will sell the package for $500 firm.

Other comments: This pistol has had between 500-600 rounds fired through it.  No malfunctions or failures.  It has been cleaned and lubricated as recommended after each range trip, hopefully it shows (see photos and feel welcome to inspect it thoroughly).  The finish is excellent as it has never been holstered and carried; after range trips it is cleaned, wiped down with a silicone cloth, and stored in a dry safe. At least around here, it is still relatively straightforward to find 40 caliber ammunition (not so for 9mm), so that's another plus.

I'd like to keep it, but I have a baby on the way in Oct, and am selling one of my XD40s.

Happy hunting! The usual rules apply: face-to-face, cash only, meet in neutral location for exchange, serious inquiries only please.
